  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      assess results of metal on metal hip replacements carried out at warwick hospital
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Resurfacing and XL head hip replacements have not done as well as expected. The ASR implant
      has been withdrawn. Recent publications and media appearances by Tony Nargol, an orthopaedic
      surgeon, have suggested 36mm metal on metal replacements. I intend to report the results of
      this series.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
